EMAlliance Buys A-Tec’s Croat Unit for $64 Million, WiBlatt Says

-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 
2011-03-20T16:25:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-20/emalliance-buys-a-tec-s-croat-unit-for-64-million-wiblatt-says.html
OAO EMAlliance, a Russian boiler
maker, has acquired Duro Dakovic, the Croatian unit of insolvent  A-Tec Industries AG (ATEC) , Wirtschaftsblatt newspaper reported, citing
Hans-Georg Kantner of Kreditschutzverband von 1870, the
spokesman for A-Tec’s creditor committee.  The Croatian boiler maker sold for about 45 million euros
($64 million), the Vienna-based paper said, citing unidentified
people familiar with the deal. Austria’s  Andritz AG (ANDR)  may also
have been interested, according to the report.  EMAlliance and Korea’s Doosan Heavy Industries and
Construction Co. both are interested in A-Tec’s AE&E unit in  Germany , which is the next A-Tec asset to be sold, the paper
said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoe Schneeweiss at 
 zschneeweiss@bloomberg.net  